The Chairman of Kuje Area Council of the FCT, Alhaji Abdullahi Suleiman Sabo, has appointed six supervisory councillors and Special Assistants (SAs) into his cabinet. Sabo, who announced the appointments in a statement made available to newsmen on Wednesday, gave the names of the supervisory councillors and their portfolios as Mr Bona Yunusa (health), David Shekwo (environment) and Emmanuel Makeri (special duties). Others are Zainab Bako Usman (education), Amos Samari (works) and Ezekiel Gimba (agriculture). The newly appointed SAs are Abubakar Jibrin (works), Afiniki Adamu (environment/sanitation), Isah Zakar (special duties), Tanko Baba Zagabutu (political matters), Kirmi Baba (health/human services) and Oladipo Hide (education/social development). The chairman, who noted that the appointments were based on merit across the 10 wards of the council, said a date would be announced for their inauguration. 